  (15672,'IE005002001005009012005000000000000000',7,1037,'Expenditure','Yes','No','Expenditure:Employee Related Cost:Municipal Staff:Salaries, Wages and Allowances:Allowances:Service Related Benefits:Overtime:Night Shift','Night Shift',3419,2,NULL,1,NULL,2,NULL,0,NULL,'N/a','ITEM','7',NULL,'N/a','All',NULL,'5085cf8c-7688-4d84-b80e-4418b0c42daa','6154cea6-83d1-4ea4-83a9-681971f06e13','Night shift allowance in general refers to work performed after 18:00 and before 6:00 the next day.  An employer may only require or permit an employee to perform night work is so agreed and if an employee is compensated by the payment of an allowance, which may a shift allowance as per the Bargaining Council Agreement, or by reduction of working hours.  Night shift allowance should not be paid out to employees who are already receiving standby allowance.  Transport is available between employees place of work at the commencement and conclusion of employees shift.',1,'v69',NULL),
